  {
    "type": "message",
    "subtype": "thread_broadcast",
    "text": "Thanks!  Well, I'm new to the field, so in part I'm just gathering impressions from what others have done.  I caught Nadia Polikarpova and James Koppel's *great* talks at Strange Loop this week.  I'm also tinkering with building my own synthesis system from the ground up, starting with a very minimal reversible machine.  My hunch is that there ought to be an advantage in enumerative and search aspects of the problem if the search space has a nice algebraic structure.",
